import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['ret'] = pd.to_numeric(data['ret'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['ret'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='ret', kde=True, ax=ax, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(data['ret'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['ret'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axvline(data['ret'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['ret'].median():.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Daily Returns')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of daily returns?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='open', y='close', data=data, ax=ax)
    ax.set_xlabel('Open Price')
    ax.set_ylabel('Close Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the correlation between open and close prices?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['signal'] = data['signal'].astype(str)
    sns.barplot(x='signal', y='ret', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.axhline(y=data['ret'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.title('What is the average daily return for each signal type?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['time'] = data['date'].dt.time
    data = data.drop(columns=['date'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data=data[['high', 'low']], ax=ax, palette='Set2')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of daily highs and lows?')
    ax.set_xlabel('High and Low')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='close', data=data, ax=ax, color='blue')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of the stock price over time?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Close Price')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
